{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":839,"text":"So how many of you have ever\nbeen in a cave before?"},{"time":3576,"text":"Okay, a few of you."},{"time":4987,"text":"When you think of a cave, most of you think"},{"time":6619,"text":"of a tunnel going through solid rock,"},{"time":8780,"text":"and in fact, that's how most caves are."},{"time":10711,"text":"Around this half of the country,"},{"time":12094,"text":"most of your caves are made of limestone."},{"time":14100,"text":"Back where I'm from, most of our \ncaves are made of lava rock,"},{"time":17048,"text":"because we have a lot of volcanoes out there."},{"time":18881,"text":"But the caves I want to share \nwith you today are made"},{"time":20931,"text":"completely of ice, specifically glacier ice"},{"time":24044,"text":"that's formed in the side of the tallest mountain"},{"time":26042,"text":"in the state of Oregon, called Mount Hood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29125,"text":"Now Mount Hood's only \none hour's drive from Portland,"},{"time":32188,"text":"the largest city in Oregon,"},{"time":33911,"text":"where over two million people live."},{"time":36140,"text":"Now the most exciting thing for a cave explorer"},{"time":38387,"text":"is to find a new cave"},{"time":39944,"text":"and be the first human to ever go into it."},{"time":42157,"text":"The second most exciting thing for a cave explorer"},{"time":44124,"text":"is to be the first one to make a map of a cave."},{"time":46555,"text":"Now these days, with so many people hiking around,"},{"time":48763,"text":"it's pretty hard to find a new cave,"},{"time":50688,"text":"so you can imagine how excited we were"},{"time":52218,"text":"to find three new caves"},{"time":53989,"text":"within sight of Oregon's largest city"},{"time":56025,"text":"and realize that they had never been explored"},{"time":58071,"text":"or mapped before."},{"time":59402,"text":"It was kind of like being an astronaut,"},{"time":60598,"text":"because we were getting to\nsee things and go places"},{"time":63285,"text":"that no one had ever seen or gone to before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66569,"text":"So what is a glacier?"},{"time":68303,"text":"Well, those of you who have\never seen or touched snow,"},{"time":70216,"text":"you know that it's really light,"},{"time":71499,"text":"because it's just a bunch of tiny ice crystals\nclumped together, and it's mostly air."},{"time":75220,"text":"If you squish a handful of snow to make a snowball,"},{"time":77630,"text":"it gets really small, hard and dense."},{"time":79828,"text":"Well, on a mountain like Hood, where it snows"},{"time":81580,"text":"over 20 feet a year,"},{"time":83361,"text":"it crushes the air out of it"},{"time":85304,"text":"and gradually forms it into hard blue ice."},{"time":88485,"text":"Now each year, more and more ice\nstacks up on top of it,"},{"time":91445,"text":"and eventually it gets so heavy"},{"time":93357,"text":"that it starts to slide down the mountain"},{"time":95143,"text":"under its own weight,"},{"time":96581,"text":"forming a slow-moving river of ice."},{"time":98879,"text":"When ice packed like that starts to move,"},{"time":101224,"text":"we call it a glacier, and we give it a name."},{"time":103334,"text":"The name of the glacier these caves are formed in"},{"time":105154,"text":"is the Sandy Glacier."},{"time":106830,"text":"Now each year, as new snow lands on the glacier,"},{"time":110283,"text":"it melts in the summer sun,"},{"time":111950,"text":"and it forms little rivers of water\non the flow along the ice,"},{"time":114809,"text":"and they start to melt and bore\ntheir way down through the glacier,"},{"time":117686,"text":"forming big networks of caves,"},{"time":119614,"text":"sometimes going all the way down\nto the underlying bedrock."},{"time":122919,"text":"Now the crazy thing about glacier caves"},{"time":124991,"text":"is that each year, new tunnels form."},{"time":128098,"text":"Different waterfalls pop up or move around"},{"time":130091,"text":"from place to place inside the cave."},{"time":132223,"text":"Warm water from the top of the ice"},{"time":134068,"text":"is boring its way down,"},{"time":135545,"text":"and warm air from below the mountain"},{"time":137485,"text":"actually rises up, gets into the cave,"},{"time":139926,"text":"and melts the ceilings back taller and taller."},{"time":142469,"text":"But the weirdest thing about glacier caves"},{"time":144596,"text":"is that the entire cave is moving,"},{"time":146702,"text":"because it's formed inside a block of ice"},{"time":148582,"text":"the size of a small city"},{"time":150273,"text":"that's slowly sliding down the mountain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152670,"text":"Now this is Brent McGregor,"},{"time":154497,"text":"my cave exploration partner."},{"time":156469,"text":"He and I have both been exploring caves a long time"},{"time":159084,"text":"and we've been climbing mountains a long time,"},{"time":161052,"text":"but neither one of us had ever really\nexplored a glacier cave before."},{"time":164132,"text":"Back in 2011, Brent saw a YouTube video"},{"time":167177,"text":"of a couple of hikers that stumbled across\nthe entrance to one of these caves."},{"time":170804,"text":"There were no GPS coordinates for it,"},{"time":172824,"text":"and all we knew was that it was somewhere"},{"time":174367,"text":"out on the Sandy Glacier."},{"time":176047,"text":"So in July of that year, we went out on the glacier,"},{"time":178646,"text":"and we found a big crack in the ice."},{"time":180624,"text":"We had to build snow and ice anchors"},{"time":182825,"text":"so that we could tie off ropes\nand rappel down into the hole."},{"time":186017,"text":"This is me looking into the entrance crevasse."},{"time":188753,"text":"At the end of this hole, we found a huge tunnel"},{"time":191304,"text":"going right up the mountain"},{"time":192795,"text":"underneath thousands of tons of glacier ice."},{"time":195328,"text":"We followed this cave back for about a half mile"},{"time":197732,"text":"until it came to an end,"},{"time":199371,"text":"and then with the help of our survey tools"},{"time":201497,"text":"we made a three-dimensional map of the cave"},{"time":203565,"text":"on our way back out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205088,"text":"So how do you map a cave?"},{"time":207146,"text":"Well, cave maps aren't like trail maps or road maps"},{"time":209874,"text":"because they have pits and holes \ngoing to overlapping levels."},{"time":213098,"text":"To make a cave map, you have to set up"},{"time":214702,"text":"survey stations every few feet inside the cave,"},{"time":217597,"text":"and you use a laser to measure\nthe distance between those stations."},{"time":220888,"text":"Then you use a compass and an inclinometer"},{"time":223327,"text":"to measure the direction the cave is headed"},{"time":225263,"text":"and measure the slope of the floor and the ceilings."},{"time":227979,"text":"Now those of you taking trigonometry,"},{"time":229709,"text":"that particular type of math is very useful"},{"time":231820,"text":"for making maps like this"},{"time":233353,"text":"because it allows you to measure\nheights and distances"},{"time":235598,"text":"without actually having to go there."},{"time":237503,"text":"In fact, the more I mapped and studied caves,"},{"time":239882,"text":"the more useful I found all that math"},{"time":241913,"text":"that I originally hated in school to be."},{"time":244155,"text":"So when you're done surveying,"},{"time":246028,"text":"you take all this data and\nyou punch it into a computer"},{"time":248455,"text":"and you find someone that can draw really well,"},{"time":251075,"text":"and you have them draft up a map"},{"time":252723,"text":"that looks something like this,"},{"time":254276,"text":"and it'll show you both a\nbird's-eye view of the passage"},{"time":257544,"text":"as well as a profile view of the passage,"},{"time":259994,"text":"kind of like an ant farm view."},{"time":261714,"text":"We named this cave Snow Dragon Cave"},{"time":263713,"text":"because it was like a big dragon\nsleeping under the snow."},{"time":266761,"text":"Now later this summer, as more\nsnow melted off the glacier,"},{"time":269273,"text":"we found more caves, and we realized\nthey were all connected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272940,"text":"Not long after we mapped Snow Dragon,"},{"time":275099,"text":"Brent discovered this new cave not very far away."},{"time":278119,"text":"The inside of it was coated with ice,"},{"time":280258,"text":"so we had to wear big spikes\non our feet called crampons"},{"time":283185,"text":"so we could walk around without slipping."},{"time":285489,"text":"This cave was amazing."},{"time":287350,"text":"The ice in the ceiling was glowing blue anad green"},{"time":289606,"text":"because the sunlight from far above"},{"time":291344,"text":"was shining through the ice and lighting it all up."},{"time":294319,"text":"And we couldn't understand why this cave"},{"time":296227,"text":"was so much colder than Snow Dragon"},{"time":297873,"text":"until we got to the end and we found out why."},{"time":300782,"text":"There was a huge pit or shaft called a moulin"},{"time":303700,"text":"going 130 feet straight up\nto the surface of the glacier."},{"time":307335,"text":"Cold air from the top of the mountain"},{"time":309146,"text":"was flowing down this hole\nand blasting through the cave,"},{"time":311960,"text":"freezing everything inside of it."},{"time":314043,"text":"And we were so excited about finding this new pit,"},{"time":316254,"text":"we actually came back in January the following year"},{"time":318562,"text":"so we could be the first ones to explore it."},{"time":321357,"text":"It was so cold outside,"},{"time":322782,"text":"we actually had to sleep inside the cave."},{"time":325040,"text":"There's our camp on the left side \nof this entrance room."},{"time":328768,"text":"The next morning, we climbed out of the cave"},{"time":331377,"text":"and hiked all the way to the top of the glacier,"},{"time":333386,"text":"where we finally rigged and rappelled this pit"},{"time":335614,"text":"for the very first time."},{"time":337381,"text":"Brent named this cave Pure Imagination,"},{"time":339468,"text":"I think because the beautiful sights we saw in there"},{"time":341485,"text":"were beyond what we could have ever imagined."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344067,"text":"So besides really cool ice,\nwhat else is inside these caves?"},{"time":347230,"text":"Well not too much lives in them \nbecause they're so cold"},{"time":349816,"text":"and the entrance is actually covered up with snow"},{"time":351826,"text":"for about eight months of the year."},{"time":353535,"text":"But there are some really cool things in there."},{"time":355471,"text":"There's weird bacteria living in the water"},{"time":357834,"text":"that actually eat and digest rocks"},{"time":360098,"text":"to make their own food"},{"time":361452,"text":"to live under this ice."},{"time":363168,"text":"In fact, this past summer, scientists collected"},{"time":365270,"text":"samples of water and ice"},{"time":367100,"text":"specifically to see if things called extremophiles,"},{"time":370035,"text":"tiny lifeforms that are evolved\nto live in completely hostile conditions,"},{"time":373874,"text":"might be living under the ice,"},{"time":375311,"text":"kind of like what they hope to find\non the polar icecaps of Mars someday."},{"time":378989,"text":"Another really cool things is that,"},{"time":380450,"text":"as seeds and birds land on\nthe surface of the glacier and die,"},{"time":383706,"text":"they get buried in the snow"},{"time":385350,"text":"and gradually become part of the glacier,"},{"time":387140,"text":"sinking deeper and deeper into the ice."},{"time":389514,"text":"As these caves form and melt \ntheir way up into the ice,"},{"time":392757,"text":"they make these artifacts rain down from the ceiling"},{"time":395206,"text":"and fall onto the cave floor,\nwhere we end up finding them."},{"time":397935,"text":"For example, this is a noble fir seed we found."},{"time":400961,"text":"It's been frozen in the ice for over 100 years,"},{"time":403186,"text":"and it's just now starting to sprout."},{"time":405895,"text":"This mallard duck feather"},{"time":407590,"text":"was found over 1,800 feet\nin the back of Snow Dragon Cave."},{"time":410911,"text":"This duck died on the surface\nof the glacier long, long ago,"},{"time":413869,"text":"and its feathers have finally made it\ndown through over 100 feet of ice"},{"time":417324,"text":"before falling inside the cave."},{"time":419508,"text":"And this beautiful quartz crystal"},{"time":421040,"text":"was also found in the back of Snow Dragon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423165,"text":"Even now, Brent and I find it hard to believe"},{"time":425437,"text":"that all these discoveries were \nessentially in our own backyard,"},{"time":428781,"text":"hidden away, just waiting to be found."},{"time":431481,"text":"Like I said earlier, the idea of discovering"},{"time":433754,"text":"in this busy world we live in"},{"time":435161,"text":"kind of seems like something \nyou can only do with space travel now,"},{"time":438061,"text":"but that's not true."},{"time":439559,"text":"Every year, new caves get discovered"},{"time":441837,"text":"that no one has ever been in before."},{"time":443602,"text":"So it's actually not too late for one of you"},{"time":445849,"text":"to become a discoverer yourself."},{"time":447710,"text":"You just have to be willing to look"},{"time":449571,"text":"and go where people don't often go"},{"time":452207,"text":"and focus your eyes and your mind"},{"time":454185,"text":"to recognize the discovery when you see it,"},{"time":456402,"text":"because it might be in your own backyard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":458733,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460587,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}